Cash Management Supervisor Job (Financial Services), Jakarta, Indonesia  -
Cash Management Supervisor Job (Financial Services), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of a growing multi-financing company. Our respected client is seeking a finance management professional for the job of Cash Management Supervisor, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The winning candidate will be responsible for handling cash-management operations, overseeing account administration, reviewing and implementing improvement in cash management, and ensuring financial obligations are met by the organization. The ideal candidate is someone who is good at analysing data, has an attention to detail and strives to find ways of investments for the company’s’ idle funds. Key job responsibilities include: Assures that the organization adheres to the company policies and procedures.Complete all cash management documentation for different departments; prepares reports and proposals for cash management improvement.Daily operations and all staff who are assigned to Cash Management.Assists in the development and implementation of custom plans to meet client's cash management.Must ensure high quality and cost effective department performance.Understand the job functions under Cash Management and must be able to perform the functions with high quality at any time.Responsible for the accounts receivable performance of the portfolio they are managing; maximizing cash, minimizing bad debt and preventing aging of receivables beyond the acceptable time frame.Gain ways to invest idle funds of the company; to increase the idle funds of the companyReconcile cash application and disbursements in a timely manner; monitors cash transactions and ensures a balanced account; forecasts and monitors cash flow in a weekly, monthly, quarterly and annual manner.Cash managers may also be responsible for preparing cash flow reports for upper management use, identifying and evaluating variances with other departments to forecast timing and amount of future cash flows, receiving transfers and handling outgoing transfers; as well as assisting in financial reporting. Job Requirements  Bachelor’s Degree (minimum) in accounting, finance or any business-related field5 years’ experience (minimum) in accounting, finance roles or corporate treasury and a couple of years in supervisory experience with proven record of success.Having experience working in a financing or banking industry is preferableRequires strong oral and written communication skillsStrong analytical and problem resolution skillsAbility to multitask and adhere to work plans and timelinesAbility to remain comfortable and composed while working under pressure in various situationsDetail-orientedEnglish language is an advantage All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to banking@monroeconsulting.com
